channel.title: For The Users of MoparScape- I Found Something
channel.description:
Hey I was world hopping buying some deaths and I thought... hey why not try world 0 i mean... That will surley get me 250. Well I wasn't expecting it to work but it did! Could this be Jagex's test server? I couldn't get past the welcome screen though... Then I had to close because it froze up. If you know why this happened please let me know. All my info came up like it would from a regular server, like my membership days left and such. If so I'm pretty sure Jagex would have special commands on that server and would be more vulnerable, such as not setting it so you don't have to be a level 3 admin to use such commands as ::item. Just letting you guys know.
~~Fuez~~

item.title: For The Users of MoparScape- I Found Something
item.dc:creator: @Dizzy Dizzy
item.description:
@Dizzy wrote:

Lol, no, the game froze up because you confused the hell out of the client. Like, one time I removed the ground code from the client and it got all confused and I got a error and froze. So, no, it’s not a test server, or you would’ve not froze. And a BIG no about the “::item” command. If they have that kinda command, it would probally be diffrent.

EDIT: Ooh, so that’s why Aryan went to world 76 every time? Becuase RegeX forgot to add random world procedure? Lol…
